The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, February 22, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Concert				 																																	(Swabhumi, February 24, 6.30 pm)				 																																	lThe Prince of Romance performs with Rahul Sharma on santoor, in tandem, after solo performances by both. In this, Claydermans first concert in Calcutta, he will showcase his vast repertoire of originals, classics and pop standards, laced with a few Bollywood hits as well				 																The Event				 																																	(Royal Calcutta Golf Club, February 23, 8 pm)				 																																	lA combination of western and Indian instruments and musicians. Divided into 10 parts, the rhythm reigns supreme with six tabla players including Subhankar Banerjee and European percussionist Ramon Lopez. Special appearance by Pandit Hari Prasad Chaurasia (picture above)				 																The Book				 																																	(Trevor Chesterfield)				 																																	lThe book in not just about one of South Africas finest bowlers told through the eyes of his close friend, but also about the countrys troubled past mirrored in the game. Through the ups and downs in his career, the book takes a closer look at South Africas political and sports history, and the lives of those in the game				 																The CD				 																																	(Mike Bloomfield amp; Al Kooper)				 																																	lThe three-night jam captured on Live Adventures is classic Bloomfield. Setting aside musical excesses that characterised that period, the talented musicians locked into the kind of telepathic collaboration that had given jamming a good name in the jazz era
